<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">

		<table width="100%">
		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    1 hand vs 2 hand weapons</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:">Anonymous</a> | 
		            11/23/1999 4:35:38 PM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">Just to in form you this is striclty opinion.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
I think that paladin's should use 1 handed blunt or slash for a number of reaon's.<BR>
<BR>
1.You attack almost twice as fast.<BR>
<BR>
As most of you have used two handed weapon's you have probly seen that you attack,they attack, they attack agian,you attack,they attack,they attack agian and then you attack and so forth very annoying if you miss twice in a row or if you a hit a weak attack.But with one handed it goes you attack,they attack,you attack,they attack and so forth.But<BR>
if you miss once or even twice or get weak hit's it won't matter as much because it will only get one or two hit's in as opposed to four.<BR>
Also depending on level the two haned weapon's aren't twice as powerfull as the one handed meaning that the attack delay difference of the one handed and two handed won't be made up by damage.<BR>
<BR>
2.The ability to use a shield will give you a ac bonus and any magical<BR>
bonuses.<BR>
<BR>
As i had said above you get a ac bonus to reduce the damage taken or block it out completly and if the shield is magical you can get any magical attributes added on.One<BR>
example is the shiny brass shield {a very popular shield found in crushbone,it's dropped by the orc trainer}which stat's are 10 ac plus 10 to magic resistance and act's like a greater light stone.<BR>
From this you get a nice amount of ac and the ability to resist magic and a nice light source.So the shield alone is almost reason enogh.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
3.The ability to bash.<BR>
<BR>
Some may say that the ability to bash is so little that it's not even worth talking about at higher<BR>
level's because your out there hitting for around a hundred damage<BR>
the 15 or so damage won't matter<BR>
much,I semi agree because let's say you hit the creature 5 times with bash before it dies that's about 75 point's of damage{if you hit for 15}which is preety good.The<BR>
bash skill comes at level 6 and you<BR>
probly already have a shield by then and if not this is a good reason to.At the lower level's bash does a nice amount of damage close to your own even.<BR>
<BR>
4.Double attack.<BR>
<BR>
The skill double attack{paladin's don't get dual wield}which will be nice with one handed or two handed weapon's.But I have found that it happen's more often with one handed<BR>
then two handed because of one simple thing,you attack more often as stated above in number one you attack almost twice as fast meaning<BR>
twice the chances to get a double attack.{by the way if you didn't know you get double attack at level<BR>
20}<BR>
<BR>
These are the main reason's {IN MY OPPINON}that a palidan should use one handed weapon's instead of two handed.
			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
			</td>
				<td>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td></tr>
