			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Um,at 24 you won't notice the exe haste effect, since it doesn't start procing until mid thirtes--I've heard anythign from 33 to 36. It's still a nice weapon though. However, this is pretty much a fact. Without dual wield, a good 1hs will NOT outdamage a good 2hs of the same relative value. Compare, say, the bladed thulian claws (5/19) to an axe of the iron back (16/37). Assuming not terrible luck--meaning the weps hit for the same percentage, more or less, you will do a great deal! more damage with the 2hs. Even dual wield, from what my 44 warrior has learned, cannot even up the gap.<BR>
Just my two cp
				</font>
			</td>

