	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Another point I haven't seen mentioned has to do with the hybrid classes. I've never played a paladin, so I don't know about that one, but I play a Shadow Knight, totally the same but the exact opposite. We get a lifetap series of spells which do a little damage and give us a little heal. Pretty nice really. I generally fire it off after every other attack. I find that it times perfectly with a nice 2hs such as axe of iron back (16/35) or my current runic carver (18/37). If I hit lifetap right after my attack, the spell fires and then my next attack comes exactly when it should. If I am using 1hs wiht a decent speed, then if I lifetap after my hit, it causes a delay before my next swing. I can tell because with the 2hs there is a slight pause after the spell fires and I swing the sword, but with 1hs the swing is pretty much immediately after the spell. So basically I'm losing a little off of the damage/delay ratio. And lifetap is fairly quick. If I want to cast Ward Undead to blast a lil skellie with 41dmg the delay is even greater.<BR>
<BR>
Probably not TERRIBLY important, just something I've noticed.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
